README for scriptbox


-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
DESCRIPTION
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

scriptbox is a simple menu creation tool for distributed bash scripting.


-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
INSTALL
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

1. create folder to store the scriptbox project files

   mkdir ~/scriptbox

2. clone the git repository of scriptbox to that directory

   git clone git://github.com/TimoL/ScriptBox.git ~/scriptbox

3. open ~/.bashrc and append the following line:
   (Note: this file may have a different name depending on your platform,
    e.g. on OSX this file is called ~/.bash_profile)

   . ~/scriptbox/scriptbox.bash

4. restart bash and you should see a small message like
   "Enabled ScriptBox 0.5.4 shell extension."

Now the scriptbox bash extension is enabled on your system.
